    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4ac2115a-7fff-41c5-e220-d817dcfedead\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed development by virtue of its position, massing and detailed design, would disrupt an unspoiled roofline</span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"> and would result in an incongruous and unsympathetic addition that would be detrimental to the character and appearance of the application dwelling and wider street scene. </span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">As such, the proposal is considered contrary to the NPPF, policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity Through the Design-Led Approach) and D4 (Delivering Good Design) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and the relevant sections Hackney’s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).</span></span><br></p>"
